 colors of barlenses are similar to those\nof normal E/S0 galaxies. Galaxy by galaxy studies show that in spiral galaxies\nvery dusty barlenses also exist, along with barlenses with rejuvenated stellar\npopulations. The central regions of galaxies are found to be on average redder\nthan bars or barlenses, although galaxies with bluer central peaks also exist.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 7 Oct 2016 15:48:03 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-03-01"}
